[Step Start] snapshot=

I have disabled the scroll-to-zoom behavior on all maps while preserving the pinch-to-zoom (trackpad) and click-and-drag interactions.

### Technical Implementation:
- **Event Filtering:** Added a custom filter to the D3 zoom behavior. It specifically intercepts `wheel` events and checks for the `ctrlKey` flag. 
    - Standard mouse wheel scrolling (which usually triggers accidental zooms while navigating the page) is now blocked.
    - Pinch-to-zoom gestures (which browsers translate to `wheel` events with the `ctrlKey` set) remain fully functional.
- **Cross-Component Consistency:** This update was applied to both the **Urban Map** (React-based `BuildingsMap` component) and the **City Pulse Map** (integrated D3 template in the backend).

This change ensures that users can scroll past map sections without getting "trapped" by accidental zooming, while maintaining full interactive control for intentional exploration.

